---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Words Ending in V: Complete Scrabble List"
  description="Complete list of valid Scrabble words ending in V. Very few English words end in V — learn them all including REV, DEV, GOV, PERV. Free, instant results."
  keywords="words ending in v, scrabble words ending in v, v ending words, rev scrabble, dev scrabble, words that end in v, v words scrabble list"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Words Ending in V: Complete Scrabble List",
    "description": "Complete list of valid Scrabble words ending in V with strategy for V-ending hooks and plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-20",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/words-ending-in-v" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many Scrabble words end in V?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Very few English words end in V. In the TWL dictionary, there are approximately 15-20 valid words ending in V, including REV, DEV, GOV, LEV, TAV, VAV, LUV, GUV, PERV, SPIV, and GANEV. SOWPODS includes additional words like DERV and OLLAV. This makes V-ending words rare and valuable knowledge for competitive play." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best V-ending plays in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The best V-ending plays exploit the rarity of these words. REV (6pts) and DEV (7pts) are quick dumps that free your rack. For higher scores, PERV (9pts) and SPIV (9pts) are 4-letter options. The real value is defensive — ending a word in V limits your opponent's hook options since very few letters can follow V to form valid words." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you hook onto a word ending in V?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Hooking onto V-ending words is extremely limited. Most words ending in V cannot take an S hook. This makes V-endings defensively strong — your opponent has very few ways to extend your word. However, some words like REV can form REVS in certain dictionaries, so always check your specific tournament dictionary." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/letter-guides/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Letter Guides</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Words Ending in V: Complete Scrabble List</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-20">June 20, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        English has a peculiar aversion to ending words with V. While hundreds of words contain V in the middle or beginning, the number that actually terminate in V is shockingly small. For Scrabble players, this rarity creates both a challenge (how do you dump a V tile late?) and an opportunity (V-endings are nearly impossible for opponents to hook). Here is every valid V-ending word you need to know.
      </p>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~20</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V-Ending Words (TWL)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V Tile Value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">V Tiles in Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">0</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Common S-Hooks</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete V-Ending Words by Length</h2>

      <p>These are all the valid Scrabble words that end in the letter V, organized by word length. Memorize the short ones first — they are your escape routes when V is stuck on your rack.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">3-Letter V-Ending Words</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">REV (6pts) — to increase engine speed · DEV (7pts) — a Hindu god · GOV (7pts) — a governor · GUV (7pts) — informal for governor · LEV (6pts) — Bulgarian currency · LUV (6pts) — informal for love · TAV (6pts) — Hebrew letter · VAV (9pts) — Hebrew letter · LAV (6pts) — lavatory</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">4-Letter V-Ending Words</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PERV (9pts) — a voyeur · SPIV (9pts) — a petty criminal · DERV (8pts) — diesel fuel (SOWPODS) · CHIV (12pts) — a knife · SHIV (10pts) — a knife · ERUV (7pts) — Jewish boundary</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">5-Letter V-Ending Words</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GANEV (9pts) — a thief · SCHAV (13pts) — a cold soup · PAREV (10pts) — kosher designation · OLLAV (8pts) — SOWPODS only</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">6+ Letter V-Ending Words</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">IMPROV (13pts) — improvisation · MAZEL TOV is not one word in Scrabble · Most 6+ letter V-endings are SOWPODS exclusives and extremely rare in tournament play</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why V-Ending Words Are Rare</h2>

      <p>English spelling conventions almost always add a silent E after V at the end of words. Think LOVE, GIVE, HAVE, MOVE — all end in VE, not V alone. The words that do end in V are mostly borrowed from other languages: Hebrew (TAV, VAV), Bulgarian (LEV), Yiddish (GANEV), or British slang (GUV, LUV).</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Linguistic Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The <span class="text-white font-medium">"no English word ends in V"</span> rule is one of the oldest spelling conventions in the language. It dates back to Middle English when scribes added -e to distinguish V from U (which shared the same character). Words like REV and GOV are modern abbreviations that break this ancient rule.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Origin: Hebrew Letters</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TAV and VAV are Hebrew alphabet letters. Both are valid in TWL and SOWPODS, making them essential V-ending knowledge for any player.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Common Mistakes</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BRAV, NARV, SOLV, GRAV — none of these are valid. Players often try abbreviations or invented words ending in V. Stick to the known list above.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for V-Ending Hooks</h2>

      <p>V-ending words are defensively powerful because they are nearly impossible to extend. Most V-ending words cannot take an S hook, and very few front hooks work either. Use this to your advantage.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Defensive V-endings:</span> When you play a word ending in V near a premium square, your opponent has almost no way to hook onto it. This protects Triple Word squares effectively — play REV or DEV next to a TW and sleep easy.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Quick V dump in endgame:</span> If you are stuck with V late in the game, REV, DEV, GOV, and LUV all use common letters (R, E, D, G, O, L, U). You will almost always have the companion letter to offload V.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">SOWPODS advantage:</span> International players have slightly more options with DERV, OLLAV, and other SOWPODS-exclusive V-endings. Know your dictionary — check whether your tournament uses TWL or SOWPODS before relying on these.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">VAV is the V-play MVP:</span> VAV scores 9 points and uses two V tiles (if you have both). Since V is worth 4 points each, getting both V tiles down in one word is highly efficient. Plus VAV on a DW square scores 18 points.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">V Tile Management</h2>

      <p>The V tile (4 points, 2 in bag) is one of the trickiest consonants to manage. It pairs poorly with other consonants and demands vowels — particularly E, A, I, and O.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 V Management Decision Tree</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Draw V → Check for VE, VA, VI combinations in longer words first (OVER, FIVE, GIVE, HAVE)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If no good VE word → Play a V-ending word (REV, DEV, GOV) to dump it efficiently</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If stuck with both V tiles → Look for VAV (uses both), VIVID, VALVE, or REVIVE opportunities</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Late game with V on rack → Exchange if 7+ tiles remain in bag. Otherwise play REV/DEV for quick dump</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pill Badges -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">V</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4 pts</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">×2</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">in bag</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">REV</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">most common</span>
        </span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
          <span class="text-white font-bold">SCHAV</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">highest pts</span>
        </span>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-points-per-letter/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Points Per Letter: Complete Tile Values Guide</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/qi-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">QI and Q Words Without U: Complete Scrabble Guide</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words: Top Plays for Maximum Points</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try these words in our free Scrabble solver — instant results, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
